<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Manager Bobby Beathard of the Washington Redskins will not return to 
the team after his contract expires May 30, a Virginia television station 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The station reported that Beathard wants to get away from football and will 
return to his home on the West Coast upon the expiration of his contract. 
</P>
<P>
The station also cited "squabbles" between Beathard and Coach Joe Gibbs as a 
factor in the general manager's decision to leave the team that he has been a 
part of since 1978. 
</P>
</TEXT>
