<P>
About 17,000 grocery workers in Northern and Central California overwhelmingly 
ratified a 3-year contract with major supermarket chains, union officials 
announced. The five locals of the United Food &amp; Commercial Workers union 
averaged 82.3% approval, said spokesman Phil Tucker. Details of the pact have 
not yet been released, pending a second ratification vote by 20,000 grocery 
workers in the Bay Area. 
