<TEXT>
<P>
The final day of a two-day strike by UC Berkeley graduate students who work as 
teaching assistants, research assistants and tutors forced the cancellation of 
75% of classes, the strikers claimed. "We were absolutely successful," said 
Colette Patt, a leader of the graduate students' association which is seeking 
UC recognition as a union. Tom Debley, a campus spokesman, said he could not 
confirm the percentage of cancellations but he said that most of the missed 
classes will be rescheduled before final exams later this month. Debley said UC 
administrators will meet soon with the teaching assistants. 
