<TEXT>
<P>
A Yorba Linda man claiming to have AIDS and with "nothing to lose" was arrested 
after a tense standoff at a Dana Point bank where he took three people hostage 
at knifepoint during a foiled robbery, authorities said. David Clyde Sweeton, 
34, a salesman who recently moved to Yorba Linda from San Juan Capistrano, 
surrendered to FBI agents and Orange County sheriff's deputies after the 
30-minute incident at a First Interstate Bank branch, officials said. His 
hostages, two female employees and a female customer, were released shaken but 
unharmed, an FBI official said. Sweeton was held in Orange County Jail on 
suspicion of bank robbery. 
