<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A deliberately set fire broke out in the office of Tehipite Middle School in 
Fresno less than 24 hours after a similar fire did extensive damage in the 
administration building at the city's Roosevelt High School. Police and fire 
investigators said there were similarities in both blazes, but initial 
investigation did not reveal links between the incidents. The middle school 
fire started in the main office, but firefighters managed to douse the flames 
quickly, limiting damage to about $4,500. Investigators said flammable liquid 
was poured on several desks and ignited. 
