<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SCUBA DIVER'S BODY FOUND OFF CATALINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's divers on Thursday found the body of a scuba diver in the waters off 
Santa Catalina Island near where he disappeared more than one week ago, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Alan Flores, 20, a Navy aviation machinist's mate and airman apprentice, 
was discovered about 10:30 a.m. off Long Point in 120 feet of water 100 yards 
from shore, Los Angeles County Sheriff's Deputy Detta Roberts said. 
</P>
<P>
Flores, who was from La Puente, was last seen April 23 while diving with 
friends, who lost sight of him in deep water about 200 yards from shore, 
Roberts said. 
</P>
<P>
Flores was on weekend leave from his base in San Diego when the accident 
occurred. 
</P>
<P>
Since his disappearance, sheriff's divers had searched the waters off Catalina, 
at one point using a sophisticated deep-water video camera on loan from Santa 
Barbara City College to scan waters as deep as 210 feet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
