METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SUSPECT CHARGED IN WOMAN'S MURDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 25-year-old man was arrested and charged in the murder of an elderly Rowland 
Heights woman who was found dead in her apartment last month, authorities said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Tony Anthony Hardin was arrested Tuesday by Los Angeles County sheriff's 
homicide detectives and arraigned Thursday in Citrus Municipal Court, Deputy 
Hal Grant said. 
</P>
<P>
Hardin was charged in the murder of Norma Barber, 66, whose body was found 
April 8 by her son at her apartment at 1900 Fullerton Road in the 
unincorporated area of Rowland Heights, Grant said. She had been strangled. 
</P>
<P>
Hardin had worked as a security guard at the apartment complex. The district 
attorney's office will seek the death penalty in the case since the murder 
allegedly occurred while Hardin was robbing the apartment, Grant said. 
</P>
