</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Penelope, an African-born lowland gorilla that produced four offspring in the 
Cincinnati Zoo's mating program, has died at age 35. 
</P>
<P>
A gift from Nobel Prize winner Dr. Albert Schweitzer, Penelope had lived at the 
zoo since 1957 and was its oldest lowland gorilla until dying Wednesday. 
</P>
