<HEADLINE>
<P>
RARE RED WOLF GIVES BIRTH TO THREE PUPPIES IN TEXAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GLEN ROSE, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A red wolf, the second-rarest mammal in the United States, gave birth to three 
puppies at a wildlife center. 
</P>
<P>
If the puppies born Wednesday survive, they will be the first Texas-born red 
wolves since the mid-1970s, raising the total population to 92, said officials 
at Fossil Rim Wildlife Center. 
</P>
<P>
The black-footed ferret is the only mammal that is rarer in the United States. 
</P>
