<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARCOS BACKERS RALLY TO DEMAND HIS RETURN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hundreds of supporters of former President Ferdinand E. Marcos staged a rally 
in Manila on Thursday to mark one year since the death of his still-unburied 
mother and to demand that Marcos be allowed to return. 
</P>
<P>
Police in San Juan, a Manila suburb, said 2,000 pro-Marcos protesters marched 
to Marcos' former home, where a Mass was celebrated in honor of his mother, 
Josefa Edralin-Marcos, who died May 4, 1988, at 95. Her family has refused to 
bury her until President Corazon Aquino allows Marcos to return from his 
Hawaiian exile to preside over the funeral. 
</P>
</TEXT>
