<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TUSTIN; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN AT BUS STOP IS HIT BY RUNAWAY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 80-year-old woman waiting at a bus stop was critically injured Thursday 
afternoon when a car idling at a nearby service station slipped into reverse 
and hit her. 
</P>
<P>
The freak accident was reported at 3:32 p.m. in the 13800 block of Red Hill 
Avenue near El Camino Real. The victim, Aletta Streeter of Tustin, was taken to 
United Western Medical Center-Santa Ana, where she was listed in critical 
condition Thursday evening. 
</P>
<P>
Driver Barbara Greeland, 45, of Santa Ana, had stopped at the Mobil service 
station on Red Hill and got out of her car to ask a question, Tustin police 
spokesman Bryan Meder said. She left her 1967 Mustang running, with the gear 
shift in park, Meder said. 
</P>
<P>
Meder said that the car slipped into reverse but that why it did so is not 
known. It moved backward at a slow speed, striking Streeter, who was sitting on 
a bus bench nearby. The runaway vehicle then entered Red Hill, colliding with a 
northbound Volvo. No injuries were reported in that accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
