<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert C. Flory, an offensive lineman from Huntington Beach, and two other 
University of Arizona football players have been placed on probation by the 
school's athletic department as a result of separate off-the-field incidents 
last month. 
</P>
<P>
Financial aid was withdrawn for seniors-to-be Flory and Donald G. Salum, an 
outside linebacker from Colorado Springs. Flory, Salum and junior-to-be 
defensive lineman Paul W. Glonek of Palos Hills, Ill., were placed on 
probation. 
</P>
<P>
Athletic Director Cedric Dempsey said legal proceedings are pending against 
Flory and Salum. 
</P>
<P>
Flory faces misdemeanor counts of resisting arrest, threats and intimidation, 
disorderly conduct and criminal damage. He was arrested at a bar after officers 
said he allegedly assaulted and threatened two men and scuffled with police. 
</P>
<P>
Flory played for the Wildcats last season, but underwent back surgery during 
the winter and Coach Dick Tomey said previously he would not play in the fall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
