THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MATER DEI DEFEATS ROSARY ON ONE-HITTER BY COBATA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Terri Cobata pitched a one-hitter as Mater Dei High School defeated Rosary, 
8-1, Thursday in an Angelus League softball game at Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
Cobata (7-4) struck out eight and didn't walk a batter. She allowed only a 
single by Jennifer Salazar in the sixth inning. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei (15-6-2 overall, 5-3-1 in league play) scored four runs in the first 
inning. Rose Imbriano had a bases-loaded triple in the inning. 
</P>
<P>
Amy Moeller had two hits and two stolen bases for Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 4, Villa Park 1 -- Sara Roberts (7-2) pitched a two-hitter, striking out 
nine, as Canyon (17-9, 7-1) moved into sole possession of first place with a 
victory at Villa Park. Seneth Thomas had two hits, including a solo home run, 
and two RBIs for Canyon. Villa Park (13-12, 6-2) falls to second place. 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 5, Katella 1 -- Tracie Noggle had a single, a stolen base and scored 
two runs, and Laura Barber scored two runs to lead Esperanza (7-12, 3-5) at 
home. 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 4, El Dorado 0 -- Sheryn Skoglund (4-3) pitched a three-hitter, 
striking out one, for Los Alamitos (12-10, 6-2) at El Dorado. The Griffins 
scored four runs in the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 2, Buena Park 0 -- Cathleen Kennedy pitched a three-hitter, striking 
out six and walking one, and had two RBIs with a bases-loaded single in the 
fourth inning for Fullerton (9-14, 3-5) at Buena Park (6-2). 
</P>
<P>
In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
Brea-Olinda 3, Anaheim 2 (10 innings) -- Natalie Stevens' two-out double drove 
in the winning run in the bottom of the 10th for Brea-Olinda (14-6, 6-2) at 
Tamarack Park in Brea. Kelly Cook (14-5) pitched a seven-hitter, striking out 
17, for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 1, Savanna 0 (11 innings) -- Danette Davis hit a solo home run with 
two outs in the bottom of the 11th to give the Tigers the victory. Natasha 
Dumoski (10-11) pitched a five-hitter, striking out 14, for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Western 9, Magnolia 0 -- Lisa Sciarrino had three hits, including a three-run 
homer, and Beth Queypo had three hits and three RBIs for the Pioneers (20-5, 
6-2). Dawn Fowler (8-4) pitched a two-hitter, striking out nine, for the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 5, Costa Mesa 0 -- Margo Melendrez (13-5) pitched a four-hitter, 
striking out 12, for the Hawks (17-6, 6-2) at Laguna Hills. Shelley Carey and 
Crissy Bulicz each hit two-run homers for Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Trabuco Hills 22, Laguna Beach 0 (6 innings) -- Linda Lunceford pitched a 
one-hitter for her second consecutive shutout as Trabuco Hills (13-11, 7-1) 
tallied 18 hits in a victory at Laguna Beach (2-6). The win ties Trabuco Hills 
with Woodbridge for first place. 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge 8, Orange 0 -- Lisa Wehren (10-6) pitched a one-hitter through five 
innings for the Warriors (14-9, 7-1) at Woodbridge. The Warriors scored seven 
runs in the first inning. Kim Johnson had two hits, including a triple, and an 
RBI for Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian 8, Orange Lutheran 1 -- Isela Duque had two hits, including 
a home run, and three RBIs for Whittier Christian (10-6, 9-3) at La Mirada 
Regional Park. Veronica Martinez (10-5) pitched a six-hitter, striking out 
four, for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
In the Century League individual golf finals: 
</P>
<P>
Steve Greenfield of Canyon shot a 150 to win the two-day tournament at Western 
Hills Country Club. Duane Jensen of Foothill and Trey Selman of Villa Park tied 
for second, as they both shot a 156. The top three qualifiers from each league 
advance to the Southern Section match, May 22 at the Canyon Country Club in 
Palm Springs. 
</P>
<P>
In the Garden Grove League individual golf finals: 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove swept the two-day tournament at El Prado Golf Course in Chino. 
Sophomore Jim Spurlock was the top finisher with a 13-over-par 157. Ken 
Wertzberger (158) and Crain Frey (160) placed second and third respectively. 
</P>
<P>
In the Pacific Coast League individual golf finals: 
</P>
<P>
Rocky Mounce of Orange shot a 14-over-par 158 to win the two-day tournament at 
Fallbrook Country Club. Mark Christensen of Trabuco Hills and Chad Fincher of 
Woodbridge tied for second with a 159. 
</P>
<P>
In the Angelus League individual tennis finals: 
</P>
<P>
Senior Dax Peterson of Mater Dei defeated his freshman brother, Adam, 6-4, 6-2, 
to win the league's singles championship at Industry Hills. Mater Dei's doubles 
team of Jason Harnett and Adam Jarrett won the doubles title. 
</P>
<P>
In Garden Grove League volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 3, Pacifica 2 -- Pat Reilly had 18 kills as La Quinta (12-3,12-0) 
won, 13-15, 15-8, 8-15, 15-8, 15-4, at Pacifica. 
</P>
<P>
In Sunset League volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Marina 3, Ocean View 1 -- Braden Coenen had 16 kills to lead Marina (12-4, 7-3) 
at home. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 3, Fountain Valley 0 -- Outside hitter Scott Drake and middle 
blocker Steve Lucas each had 13 kills to help Huntington Beach (14-2, 9-1) 
clinch the league title in three games, 15-3, 15-9, 15-12. 
</P>
