<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: CALIFORNIA REAL ESTATE MAGAZINE AIMS EXCLUSIVELY AT THE JAPANESE 
MARKET; 
</P>
<P>
REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japanese real estate investors can let their fingers do the walking. A new 
magazine pitched to them, California Real Estate Guide, will come off the 
presses in May. 
</P>
<P>
Based in Costa Mesa, the guide will feature ads in Japanese on California 
commercial buildings and residences. 
</P>
<P>
The magazine says it will have a mailing list of 2,500 real estate companies, 
banks, trading firms and individuals in Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
