<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT / COMMERCIAL REAL ESTATE: A WEEKLY LOOK AT OFFICE AND INDUSTRIAL REAL 
ESTATE IN THE COUNTY.; 
</P>
<P>
FOCUS: CENTERPOINTE LA PALMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Centerpointe La Palma is a 42-acre, $100-million, mixed-use office park at 
Orangethorpe Avenue and Valley View Street in La Palma. When the third phase is 
completed at the end of the year, the complex will include 11 office buildings, 
ranging from single-story to seven stories, a 162-room Day's Inn hotel, four 
restaurants, 34,000 square feet of retail space and a three-level parking 
garage. 
</P>
<P>
FACTS AND FIGURES 
</P>
<P>
Address: 1 Centerpointe Drive, La Palma 
</P>
<P>
Developer: Birtcher 
</P>
<P>
Architect: Ware &amp; Malcomb Architects, Irvine 
</P>
<P>
Primary Contractor: Birtcher Construction 
</P>
<P>
Financing: Joint venture of the Mutual Life Insurance Co. of New York Real 
Estate Investments and Birtcher 
</P>
<P>
Square feet: 375,000 office; 256,000 R&amp;D 
</P>
<P>
Use: Office, R&amp;D, retail, restaurant, hotel 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled completion date: December, 1989 
</P>
<P>
Percentage of building leased: 90% (Phases 1 &amp; 2) 
</P>
<P>
Parking capacity: 4 per 1,000 square feet 
</P>
<P>
Projected rental cost per sq. ft.: $1.05 for R&amp;D; $1.80 for office 
</P>
<P>
MAJOR TENANTS 
</P>
<P>
Automated Data Processing: 53,000 Square feet 
</P>
<P>
Federal Home Loan Bank of San Francisco: 37,000 Square feet 
</P>
<P>
Northern Telecom: 21,000 Square Feet 
</P>
<P>
Frontier Bank: 17,500 Square Feet 
</P>
<P>
Source: Laer Pearce &amp; Associates 
</P>
<P>
</P>
